  </alternatives>
 </inline-formula> are the DREs predicted by model 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic> for particle bin 
 <italic class="italic">k</italic> at longitude 
 <italic class="italic">θ</italic> and latitude 
 <italic class="italic">ϕ</italic>, due to interactions with SW and LW radiation, respectively, and 
 <italic class="italic">N</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">k</italic>,
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>
 </sub> denotes the number of particle bins simulated by climate model 
 <italic class="italic">i</italic>. This calculation is averaged over a large number (
 <italic class="italic">N</italic>
 <sub class="sub">p</sub> = 10
 <sup class="sup">4</sup>) of realizations of the correction factor 
 <italic class="italic">α</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">i</italic>,
  <italic class="italic">k</italic>
 </sub>, which equals
 <disp-formula id="Equ9" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">9</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M61" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$\alpha _{i,k} = \frac{{\hat \tau _{{\mathrm{d}},k}}}{{\tau _{{\mathrm{d}},i,k}}}.$$\end{document}</tex-math>
